psalm.text:
[[Ps 56,2]]Have mercy on me, O God, for men trample upon me;
all the day they press their attack against me.
[[Ps 56,3]]My adversaries trample upon me all the day;
yes, many fight against me.

[[Ps 56,9]]My wanderings you have counted;
my tears are stored in your flask;
are they not recorded in your book?
[[Ps 56,10a]]Then do my enemies turn back,
when I call upon you.

[[Ps 56,10b]]Now I know that God is with me.
[[Ps 56,11]]In God, in whose promise I glory,
in God I trust without fear;
what can flesh do against me?

[[Ps 56,12]]I am bound, O God, by vows to you;
your thank offerings I will fulfill.
[[Ps 56,13]]For you have rescued me from death,
my feet, too, from stumbling;
that I may walk before God in the light of the living.
